<h2 id="productivity-inspiration">Productivity Inspiration</h2>
<ul>
<li>Alessandro Farace explains his Obsidian flashcard workflow in <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/alessandrofv.bsky.social/post/3lcdno6i3he2o" target="_blank">this detailed Bluesky thread</a>. He uses 5 plugins while my flashcard method uses none. Each way of doing things has its own pros and cons.</li>
<li>Nerdy Momo Cat answers the question<span class="push-double"></span> <span class="pull-double">‚Äú</span>Can you do with just an Apple-based digital information setup?‚Äù with <a href="https://nerdymomocat.github.io/posts/apps-by-apple-ecosystem/" target="_blank">this extensive, well-structured list of apps</a>. It is beautifully opinionated and mentions some extensions and keyboard shortcuts I either didn‚Äôt know about or had forgotten.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RZnlUAPccaA" target="_blank">This 39 second video</a> reminded me of the biggest Why behind the pursuit of productivity: gaining the time needed to be a positive presence in the life of someone else. I do enjoy a regular wakeup to the fact that <em>productivity is not and end in and of itself</em>.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="paper-or-paperless-how-about-both">Paper, or paperless? How about both</h2>
